<p>OTP start script example for Unix.</p><h2 id="description" class="section-heading">
  <a href="#description" class="hover-link">
    <i class="ri-link-m" aria-hidden="true"></i>
  </a>
  <span class="text">Description</span>
</h2>
<p>The <code class="inline">start</code> script is an example script on how to start up the Erlang system in
embedded mode on Unix.</p><p>For more information about the use, see the
<a href="../../../lib/../system/doc/html/embedded.html">Embedded System User's Guide</a> in System
Documentation.</p><pre><code class="text">start [ data_file ]</code></pre><p>Argument:</p><ul><li><strong><code class="inline">data_file</code></strong> - Optional. Specifies what <code class="inline">start_erl.data</code> file to use.</li></ul><p>Environment variable <code class="inline">RELDIR</code> can be set before calling this example, which sets
the directory where to find the release files.</p><h2 id="see-also" class="section-heading">
  <a href="#see-also" class="hover-link">
